{{unreferenced|date=October 2012}}

'''Aleksander Gieysztor''' (July 17, 1916, [[Moscow]], [[Russian Empire]] &mdash; February 9, 1999, [[Warsaw]], [[Poland]]) was a Polish historian [[medievalist]], decorated with the [[Order of the White Eagle (Poland)|Order of the White Eagle]] (1994) and Commander's Cross with Star of the  [[Order of Polonia Restituta]] (1993).

He was born in Moscow in Polish family. He was living in Warsaw since 1921. In 1937 he graduated in history at [[Warsaw University]].

Gieysztor  is the namesake of the Aleksander Gieysztor Prize of the Kronenberg Foundation and the [[Aleksander Gieysztor Academy of Humanities]].

== Books ==
*''Ze studi<U+00F3>w nad genez<U+0105> wypraw krzy<U+017C>owych'' (1948)
*''Mitologia S<U+0142>owian'' (1982)

